



Sir,
Cambridge 2d March76. Saturday Evening



After weighing all Circumstances of Tide &ca& considering the hazard of having the Posts on Dorchester Neck taken by the Enemy, & the evil consequences which would result from it, the Gentlemen here, are of Opinion that we should go on there Munday Night.1 I give you this Early notice of it, that you may delay no time in preparing for it, as every thing here will be got in readiness to co-operateIn haste I am Sr Yr most Obedt Servt

Go: Washington


Remember the Barrels.2

